Query the two cities in STATION with the shortest and longest CITY names, as well as their respective lengths (i.e.: number of characters in the name). If there is more than one smallest or largest city, choose the one that comes first when ordered alphabetically.

shortest city;

SELECT city,length(city) from station order by length(city), city limit 1;

longest city;

SELECT CITY, LENGTH(CITY)
FROM STATION
ORDER BY LENGTH(CITY) DESC, CITY
LIMIT 1;

//We use LIMIT 1 to make sure only one row is returned from the query.

Why itâ€™s needed here

Your query orders the cities by length (and alphabetically for ties).
After sorting, the first row is the correct answer.

ORDER BY LENGTH(CITY), CITY
LIMIT 1;


//This means:

Sort cities by shortest length first

If lengths are equal, sort alphabetically

Pick the first row only
